Recommended Enterprise Enhancements

To make MyPA suitable for production and future SaaS deployment, consider including:

Multi-tenancy: Each business has isolated data using a business_id partitioning strategy.
Subscription tiers: Free, Basic, Premium, and Enterprise plans with feature flags and usage limits.
Payment gateway integration: Support providers such as Razorpay, Cashfree, or PhonePe for subscription billing.
Real-time notifications: Use WebSockets (e.g., Socket.IO) for instant payment updates and customer notifications.
Background jobs: Queue email, SMS, report generation, and synchronization tasks using a job queue such as BullMQ.
API versioning: Prefix endpoints with /api/v1 to allow future evolution without breaking clients.
Comprehensive auditing: Record every create, update, delete, login, and permission change for compliance.
Automated testing: Unit, integration, and end-to-end tests using Jest and Supertest.
Deployment-ready configuration: Docker, Docker Compose, CI/CD pipelines, environment-based configuration, centralized logging, and health-check endpoints.

This specification provides a solid foundation for KIRO to generate a scalable, enterprise-grade React + Express + MySQL/SQLite application with clear separation of concerns between the frontend, backend, and REST API layers.